inn1.comm: short ball to begin with, Hayden's not on the ball and pulls into the ground and the ball rolls to short fine leg
but this is better from Hayden, as he rocks back to another short-pitched delivery outside off stump and pulls through midwicket for one out to the sweepers on the boundary
good length delivery on middle and leg, he just taps that into the on side and sets off the single
back of a length down leg stump, Hayden eases it off the pads wide of square leg for an easy couple of runs
better ball, moving away from Hayden on a good length, who plants the front foot forward and shoulders arms
good stuff again, comes back in from outside off stump and carries on over the top of off stump as Hayden shoulders arms again
fullish, swinging delivery that moves well past him outside off stump, no need to play at that
moving across him off the scrambled seam, but much closer to off stump and Watson shoulders arms to that
even closer to the stumps and now Watson has to play at it, coming forward on the move and then defending into the covers
lovely ball! Angled across him on a sweet length and Watson pokes at it tentatively, getting beaten by the movement
the attempted yorker goes awry, coming in a tad fuller on middle and leg than he would've liked, and Watson chips it into midwicket for a quick single
fullish, outside off stump, and Hayden judges it to perfection and shoulders arms
back of a length outside off stump and moving in, Watson gets behind the line and defends to the off
back of a length and wider this time, though its quicker - 134ks - and Watson has to check his attempted cut to guide it to point
shorter and wider, Watson neatly runs that wide of backward point for one out to Franklin at wide third man
full on the legs and Hayden clips that past square leg out to Fulton, running around from the deep, who just cant time his dive right and the ball wins that race
better stuff, on a length just around off stump, and Hayden has to desist the flick and come forward to defend instead
good length outside off stump and he checks his drive back to Tuffey
short of a length outside off stump, Watson stands up and plays it late, in front of point, but resists going for the run as Vincent swoops in and fires a throw back to the 'keeper
back of a length outside off stump, Watson punches that nicely down the ground and sets off, but Patel at mid-off dives full stretch and stops it
wider and fuller outside off stump, Watson gets down on one knee and drives, but gets beaten
almost! Watson gets ambitious, getting under a back of a length delivery on middle and leg that skids onto him, heaving it up in the air and luckily it lands safely in no man's land out near long-off
good length on middle and leg and he checks the drive to mid-on
a tad fuller on the stumps, Watson walks into a defensive push back past the bowler but the ball slows up near the ropes and its just two
room offered outside off stump but Hayden's timings all wrong and he cant cash in with the cut shot
overpitched, he gets to the pitch and drives nicely but cant beat Taylor at cover
down leg stump, he clips it just in front of short fine leg and calls for the run, Watson replies with ease and thats one
short and wide from Tuffey, and Watson gets up on the toes and cracks it in front of square for four, smack of the middle of the horizontal bat
short of a good length on middle and off, up he goes again and just rolls the wrists on it to pick up an easy single in front of square leg
good length outside off stump, he leans into a soft drive in front of mid-off and calls for the quick single
fraction short outside off stump and Hayden brings the bat down like a rapier, cutting hard past a diving Vincent at point and thats four all the way, shot!
back of a length outside off stump, no real movement, and Hayden shoulders arms
short of a length and moving down the legs, just where he likes 'em, all he has to do is clip it off the pads backward of square and in the gap to pick up four more
good length outside off stump, he leaves it be for McCullum to collect
short of a length on off stump, stands up a tad, Hayden too gets up and punches down the ground but the ball hits the stumps at the other end
driveable length outside off stump, he does so but cant beat Fulton at short extra cover
good length delivery on off stump, Watson brings his weight forward and over the ball, then works it into the on side for a quick single
back of a length and moving away from middle and leg, and Hayden comes forward and defends into the covers
good length on middle and leg, he flicks into midwicket but cant beat the man there
good length and pacier on off stump, he comes forward and works it to the on side where Tuffey dives full stretch to his left but cant get a hand to it, mid-on moves in quickly
pitched up outside off stump, fractionally, and he drives it to mid-off
good stop! Hayden drives on off middle and off stump towards mid-on, where an energetic Patel throws himself full length and saves runs
pitched up and he drives back down the ground, but Franklin gets a boot on it and deflects it
back of a length on the stumps, Watson gets behind the line and defends back to Franklin
fullish delivery moves in from just outside off stump, Watson drives but gets an inside-edge to midwicket, and calls for the run
overpitched outside off stump and he drives it straight to short extra cover
back of a length outside off stump, he gets onto the backfoot and opens the face, running it down to third man for one
short of a good length on middle and leg, whipped off the backfoot through midwicket for two
back of a length outside off stump, he runs it straight to backward point
good length on the stumps, he gets up and looks to manufacture runs on the leg side but cant beat short midwicket
back of a length on leg stump, easy stuff for Hayden to work into the leg side for one
back of a length on leg stump, he tries the tip-and-run but bowler and 'keeper are quick
moves in off a length and he adjusts to run it fine, backward point moves in but they take on Taylor's arm for the single
good length outside off stump, he comes to the pitch and drives past mid-off for long-off to come forward and collect
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and defends to point with a firm 'NO, MATE' back to Watson
shot! Pitched up fractionally and he gets on top of it, rolling the wrists to drive it wide of the stumps and down the ground for four
four more, as he gets on top of a short-pitched delivery and slams it over mid-on
driveable length outside off stump but he cant cash in this time, finding cover again
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and defends to cover
good length again, he waits and plays it softly back to Franklin's right
back of a length outside leg stump, Watson's already backed away, in hopes of whacking one over cover, and has to adjust to nudge it around the corner for one
shortish length outside off stump, Hayden's coming forward and has to adjust to steer it to backward point
good length delivery on off stump, a tad slower perhaps, and Hayden defends solidly off the front foot
good length on off stump again but this time he pushes with soft hands to mid-off and picks up a single to get Watson on strike
good length just outside off stump, he comes forward and flicks to midwicket
bang, thats four! The slower one is just overpitched enough for Watson to free the front leg and smash that down the ground cleanly
not the best ball to begin with, down leg stump and Hayden clips past square leg for the single
fuller outside off stump, but Watson watches it carefully into McCullum's gloves
short and wide, he rocks back and places that nicely in the gap between cover and point for another boundary
short and wide again, not the way to bowl in the PowerPlays, and Watson gets right over it, cutting superbly backward of point for another four
again he drops short but is lucky to get away with it, as Watson's checked backfoot drive doesnt beat cover
lands this one fuller and wider and Watson goes through with the flashy backfoot drive, as he knew there was no slip, and the ball races away off the thick edge for four more
flat down the leg side and Hayden stands tall to punch into midwicket for one
tossed up outside off stump, Watson comes forward and defends back to Patel
flatter trajectory, he shuffles across and taps it in front of square leg for one
quicker one, on middle and leg, and Hayden jams the bat down on it
drifts down leg stump and he clips it past short fine leg for one
flat outside off stump, Watson comes forward and makes it fuller to drive to mid-on for one more
overpitched outside off stump, he comes to the pitch and drives to mid-off
outside off stump and its steered down to third man
back of a length outside off stump, no room to cut but he does so anyways, cramped for it, and gets an inside-edge near off stump, Watson wants the single and gets it, well run
full outside off stump, Watson looks to get forward but adjusts and square-drives that excellently in the gap at point for four, lovely to watch!
slower ball on a good length, he waits for it and then opens the face to steer it past backward point
quicker on a good length outside off stump, Hayden covers off stump and leaves it be
back of a length outside off stump, Watson stands and defends to point
back of a length on middle and off, Watson rolls the wrists over it, placing it wide of square leg and calling for the single
good length outside off stump, good line, Hayden comes forward and drives to cover
shorter this time, he comes forward and drives out to long-off for one
he gives himself some room to hit it offside, Styris follows him by bowling it down leg, Watson has to adjust to play it leg side and a misfield at short fine leg gives up the boundary
back of a length outside off stump, he runs it off the face of the bat for one down to third man
back of a length outside off stump, Watson opens the face to squirt that through gully out to Tuffey on the run from third man
back of a length around off stump, Hayden comes forward and then has to defend back to Gillespie
good length just outside off stump, he comes forward again and checks the drive
strays down leg stump and Hayden clips into midwicket for one
overpitched just outside off stump and he drives back to Gillespie, who jumps up and collects with his right hand
short and wide, he cuts and gets un under-edge past McCullum to bring up his 50, well played
quick, on a length outside off stump, Watson runs it to point
back of a length outside off stump, driven to cover
back of a length again, this time he drives back down past the stumps to long-off for one
overpitched outside off stump and Hayden leans into a drive to mid-off for another easy single
drifts down leg stump, Watson plays it softly around the corner to short fine leg for one
good length outside off stump, he opens the face and places it past a diving Vincent at backward point for one
overpitched on off stump, he drives back to Gillespie who then throws back over the stumps to McCullum
full again, he drives with an inside-edge to mid-on
overpitched in the same spot again, and this time his drive hits the stumps at the other end and forces the umpire to take evasive action
short outside off stump, Watson pulls hard through square leg out to the man on the ropes, on the bounce
back  of a length on leg stump, up goes Hayden, working it past mid-on and calling for two immediately
yorker-length ball outside off stump goes past his bat and McCullum collects
back of a length on off stump, driven to mid-on
fuller this time and he drives to mid-on, but gets the quick single this time
back of a length outside off stump, he shuffles and rolls the wrists over it, placing it wide of McMillan at square leg
overpitched on off stump, Watson comes forward and chips it in the air but safely past mid-on out to a wide long-on
movement outside off stump, steered to backward point
good length outside off stump, Hayden stands and fishes at it and gets beaten, McCullum whips off the bails
flat outside off stump, Watson rocks back and cuts past point out to the sweeper
tossed up outside off stump, he comes forward and defends
fired in on leg stump, he flicks to mid-on
flat and speared into middle and leg, Hayden defends back to Patel
tossed up on off stump, he steers that to point
tossed up on middle and leg, Hayden drives to midwicket and sets off for the run, Vincent moves in and fires in a throw and Hayden gets back into his crease
good length on the stumps, he stands and works that to midwicket
good length outside off stump, he leans into a drive to cover
width offered, he cuts late, and hard, in the gap behind square for one
good length on off stump, he comes onto the front foot and flicks into midwicket to bring up the 100
width offered again, but this time Hayden cant time his cut past Vincent
dropped short outside off stump, Hayden rocks back and pulls along the ground through midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, he comes forward and squeezes that into the covers for one
flatter one this time, Watson shuffles well across and flicks to Taylor at midwicket, and sends back an eager Hayden
tossed up outside off stump, Watson uses the feet to meet the ball and drive to cover
flatter on middle and leg, he uses the feet again and flicks into midwicket
spins into him and leaves, squaring him up as he looks to work it to leg and the ball rolls to point
tossed up on middle and leg, worked past mid-on for the single
good length on the stumps, driven down to long-on for one
close! Slower ball from Sytris on a good length, Watson comes forward and stops the shot, the ball goes up in the air and lands safely in front of Tuffey between mid-off and mid-on
width offered and Hayden cuts to backward point
good length ball on the stumps, he drives back to Styris
full and wide, he gets onto one knee and really reaches for it, driving to cover
good length outside off stump, Hayden uses the feet to meet it and drives to mid-off
tossed up on leg stump, Hayden works it to Vincent at midwicket and set off, and Watson gets home by an inch as a good throw comes in
comes down the track, using his feet well, and slams it down the ground for four
spinning away outside off stump, Watson steers that wide of point for one more
comes down the track, Patel fires it in quicker and flatter, and Hayden has to work it to midwicket
tossed up again, Hayden comes down and drives back to Patel, who collects and has a shy back at Hayden
flat outside off stump, chipped into the mid-off region for one to keep strike
full outside off stump, Hayden gets down on one knee and square-drives out to the sweeper for one, and thats his 50
good length on off stump, Watson gets over it and drives down to long-on for one
back of a length outside off stump, he works that wide of midwicket for two, well run
good length outside off stump, driven out into the deep
short of a length outside off stump, he stands tall and whips that to midwicket
fuller on the stumps, he gets well over it and flicks past short fine leg for one more
full outside off stump, he comes forward and flicks to midwicket
drifts onto middle and leg and Watson works it backward of square for the single
tossed up on off stump, Hayden gets down and sweeps hard through square leg

he's got him! Quicker and flatter, doesnt turn as Watson goes back, looking to play it square, and catches him in front of middle and leg, and umpire Baxter lifts the finger as bowler and 'keeper appeal
fired in quickly on off stump, Haddin plays it back to Patel
tossed up outside off stump, he reaches for it and drives to mid-off
good length outside off stump, Hayden rocks back and cuts to backward point
short again, this time he cuts harder but cant beat point
quicker and fuller, Hayden jams the bat down with no foot movement and for the third ball in a row finds Vincent
now he's getting impatient! Makes room to cut a goodlength delivery outside off stump and very nearly chops onto off stump
back of a length just outside off stump, Haddin stands up and defends in front of point
fuller outside off stump, Haddin drives nicely to mid-off but cant beat the man there
tossed up, Hayden comes forward and gets beaten in the flight and has to adjust
tossed up again, he comes forward and defends
bang, thats half a dozen! Patel tosses it up invitingly, Hayden uses the feet nicely to come down and pick it up off a length, and send it rows back over long-off, god way to break the shackles
tossed up down leg side, Hayden goes on the backfoot and turns it to square leg
tossed up on the stumps, Haddin comes on the frontfoot and defends it solidly
fired into middle and leg, Haddin drives down to long-on to open his account
slower ball outside off stump, Haddin leans into it and drives to cover
well wide of off stump, and full, Haddin reaches for it and steers it to backward point
back of a length on leg stump, Hadding shuffles and flicks into midwicket for one
good length on middle and off, he looks to flick, getting a long way down the track, but isnt in control of that shot
short of a length outside off stump, Hayden makes room to cut and gets an inside-edge back past leg stump
short and wide, this time he times the cut nicely and gets one out to the sweeper
hello! Hayden heard Mick, is it! He slams a halfvolley from McMillan straight back down the ground for four
good length on the legs, worked past midwicket for a couple
dropped! Hayden slams this very hard back to McMillan, who takes it smack in the stomach but cant hold onto it
good length outside off stump, he leans into it and drives past mid-off
slower on on the legs, Hadding clips to mid-on for one more
fullish on the legs, clipped past midwicket for one and he will retain strike
good length outside off stump and a leaden-footed Hayden swings the kitchen sink at it, but that was nuttin' but air
straighter one on the stumps, he drives down to mid-on for one
overpitched outside off stump, Haddin strokes that smack down the ground and McMillan covers good ground at long-on and stops it on the ropes
short of a length outside off stump, he has a swing at it and gets an inside-edge onto the thighs
good length outside off stump, he leans into a drive and squeezes it to mid-off
good length outside off stump, Haddin opens the face of the bat and looks to run it down
six more! Hayden gives himself room outside leg stump and has a full swing off the arms, and tees-off for maximum over long-off
overpitched outside off stump, he heaves it again but mistimes the drive back past McMillan
now Haddin wakes up, getting down on one knee and heaves across the line, finding the gap at deep backward square leg and thats four
good length outside the off stump, he comes forward and drives past mid-off for two
whoof! Shot! Halfvolley outside off stump, Haddin just disdainfully heaves that off one knee for a dinger over wide long-on
beaten! Quicker one outside off stump, comes in as Haddin flirts at it and McCullum whips off the bails
fullish on middle and leg, whipped to square leg for two
fullish on middle and off, Hayden drives back past the stumps and McMillan does well on the ropes to save two runs
short of a length outside off, Hayden goes on the backfoot and cuts it to deep backward point
back of a length on middle and leg, Haddin works it to deep midwicket for one
good length outside off stump, Hayden opens the face of the bat and steers it to point
good length delivery, Hayden goes back in defense
and he begins with a full toss outside off stump, which Haddin creams to the long-off fence for four
overpitched this time, Hadding leans into it and drives, cover gets a hand to it and parries it towards mid-off
good length on middle and off, Hayden works it straight to mid-on
good ball! Fires in the spot-on yorker and Hayden does well to jam the bat down in the nick of time, well bowled, sir
this time the yorker becomes a full toss that Hayden tamely drives to mid-off
another full toss, which Haddin drives past Gillespie for a brace out to Patel at long-off
full outside off stump, Hayden exposes the stumps and swings at it, and the result is a genuine french-cut past leg stump for four
straighter one, and for what seems like the umpteenth time a Hayden drive hits the nonstrikers stumps and ricochets for run, and now he's into the nineties
good length outside off stump, he defends into the covers
full outside off stump, down on one knee he goes, square-driving right to a diving Vincent at point
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden plans the front leg forward and checks a tame drive back to Franklin, who's bowled a fine spell here
half-volley outside off stump, Hayden eases into a good-looking drive to Taylor back on the circle, but doesnt run the single
full just outside off stump, Haddin opens the leg and slams it straight down the ground for four, well struck
full toss on off stump, he makes room and drives past the covers out to the sweeper in the deep
well bowled, full in the slot, Hayden rolls the wrists over it and flicks into square leg
full again, no room on offer, Haddin backs away to leg and squirts this into the covers for the single
full toss! Its outside off stump, well above the waist so its a no-ball, but Hayden's taken by surprise, and heaves across the line, the ball lands in front of Patel at mid-on
another full toss, down leg, and Hayden helps it on its way to fine leg, well done
good length on middle and off, driven wide of mid-on to keep strike next over
good length ball on middle and leg, worked into mid-on for one and he moves to 98
good ball! Slower on in the blockhole, a good yorker, but Haddin digs it out and pinches the run, good stuff all round
another yorker length delivery on the stumps, Hayden gets over it and works it into midwicket and he's onto 99
full outside off stump, Haddin shuffles across the stumps and then has to jam the bat down it, steering it to backward point
full on the legs, he works it to square leg and sets off, Haddin at the other end falls over and Hayden's caught in the middle of the pitch, but a wayward throw gets him a life...madness!
there's the ton! Hayden drives a good length delivery towards mid-off and celebrates another ODI hundred! Its been a controlled innings from the big man
fires on in from around the wicket, moving down leg, Hayden exposes the stumps as he looks to lap it fine, gets rapped on the back leg but the ball looked to have been carrying on down leg
fires in another yorker well down leg stump, Hayden's backed away and as he looks to flick he cops another one on the foot and he's in pain
a low full toss on the legs is clipped square through midwicket out to Taylor on the ropes
he heaves one across the line out to the man on the ropes, moving across from wide long-on, who saves four with a good stop
well done! A yorker on off stump, which he digs out to point
halfvolley outside off stump, Haddin makes room and drives out to deep cover
low full toss outside off stump, he swings across the line but cant beat mid-on
full outside off stump, Hayden frees the arms but thats just one out to long-off
full outside off stump, he too frees the arms but in this case, its a well-timed drive through the gap at cover-point for four
gone! Tuffey rolls the fingers over it, landing it on a good length outside off stump, Hayden drives across the line and finds Vincent stationed on the circle at mid-on
good length ball on off stump, Hodge comes forward and defends to cover
back of a length outside off stump, Hodge waits for it and steers it to backward point for a risky single
back of a length outside off stump, Hodge initially comes forward and the waits for it, late-cutting between point and backward point, he sets off but hurries back in time
well bowled, as he sees Hodge come down the track, fires it full and wide, and Hodge shuffles to flick into midwicket
he uses the feet, Patel fires it full and fast, but Hayden has enough room to drive that down to long-off
oh ho! Patel tosses it up on a good length, Hodge comes down the track, gets to the pitch and smokes that handsomely over long-on for el sixo
the full toss is worked into the off side for one
tossed up on middle and leg, Hayden advances and chips over mid-on out to Tuffey moving in, but he cant get there in time
wow! Full on the legs, bread and butter, Hayden just whips that over deep backward square leg for half a dozen
full outside off stump, he doesnt move his feet and just hammers that out to long-off
good ball, yorker in the blockhole which he defends back to Styris
back of a length outside off stump, he stands and pulls along the ground through squar leg for one
fullish outside off stump, Hodge drives past mid-off for the single
bludgeoned! In the slot to be hit, and even a man on one leg can just free the arms and smoke that rows back over wide long-on, what a shot!
good length on middle and off, driven out to long-on for one
jeez! Patel floats this up, Hayden stands and swings at it, golf-style, and even though he isn't to the pitch he hammers it over long-on for six
theres nothing in this pitch! Tossed up in the blockhole and Hayden repeats the last shot for a blistering six over long-on again
fires in a low full toss on leg stump, which Hayden flicks out past square leg for one
bowled 'em neck and crop! Patel fires in one quicker as Hodge advances down the track, he's not to the pitch and the ball creeps in past the bat to shatter off and middle
tossed up on middle and leg, worked past short fine leg for one to get off the mark immediately
good length outside off stump, he leans into it and drives out to long-off
back of a length outside off stump, he frees the arms and slaps that over Styris' head for four, hard hit that
back of a length outside off stump, driven down to long-off for the single
straight on the stumps, he shuffles and works it in the gap behind square and calls for two immediately
good length outside off stump, Hussey walks into it and places it in front of point for one
good ball in the blockhole, a leaden-footed Hayden can only drive back to Styris
fired in down leg, Hussey shuffles and works it past square leg for one
the first wide, and second extra, of the innings comes as Patel fires on well down leg stump
fired in flat outside off stump, Hayden cant get the feet going and slams it down to long-off on the bounce
good length on middle and leg, he uses the feet well to meet the ball and work it wide of mid-on
fired in on middle and leg, spins into him as he makes room and he can only drive back to Patel
tossed up outside off stump, ends up a knee-high full toss, which Hayden disdainfully slams over long-on for half a dozen
quicker and flatter, he drives out to long-off for one
the yorker ends up a low full toss down leg, he's made room and swings at it, misses and a bye is the call
Hussey joins in on the fun, coming down the track to a fullish delivery, making it fuller, and short-arm-punching it flat over long-on for six, shot!

this time he's gone! Hussey again dances down to a full delivery, but gets under and rolls the wrists on it, the ball takes the leading edge and the ball pops up high in the air for McCullum to call for it and safely pouch it
full outside off stump, driven down to long-off for one
good length outside off stump, White walks into it and places it in front of point but sends back Watson, the runner
full on the legs, White looks to flick square but ends up placing it more towards midwicket
fired in full outside off stump, he swings across the line with one hand and gets it to mid-on
whats that now? White tries to club the cover off the ball but is beaten by the flight and pace, and McCullum fumbles the collection...wasnt a stumping, but still...
fired in again, on the stumps, he comes down but isnt to the pitch, works it to mid-on for one
hello dollie! Another full toss, he gets under it, doesnt time it at all but has enough bat on it to get six number eight over wide long-on
smashed down to long-off, where Vincent is almost pushed back over the ropes by the velocity of that shot as he fields it...wuff
fired in quickly, White manages to jam the bat down on it, well bowled
bowled, in the blockhole, Hayden's confused as he swings at it and the ball takes the edge to the off side
six for White! Lands on a back fo a length on the stump and he swings it away over deep midwicket for six of his own, oh boy, what next??
even better! White tees-off and sends this dinger sailing miles over long-off and thats the 15th six of the innings so far, carnage!
not this time! A bad ball but White cant send another full toss over deep midwicket as he finds Styris about three feet inside the wide long-on ropes
good length on middle and leg, worked past square leg for one
and he's off the mark first ball, driving a good length delivery from Gillespie down to long-off
comes forward to a full delivery and works it wide of mid-on, they run hard and push for two and get it
good length delivery outside off stump, driven down to long-off for one
good length outside off stump, he stands and drives down to long-off for one more and thats the highest score for an Aussie against New Zealand in one-day cricket
oh, hello! What timing! Voges takes this from just outside off stump and sends it flat as a whistle over mid-on for his first ODI six
good length outside off stump, steered towards point for the single
make that nine sixes for Hayden! He clears the leg, backing away and making room to smote that very, very high over long-off for maximum over the sight screen
full delivery outside off stump, he gets the bat down and pushes into the covers
full toss outside the off stump, again he just stands erect and drives in the gap on the off side and the ball races away to the ropes
this was in the slot to be creamed over the onside but Hayden's moved so far outside leg stump that he gets a leg bye off the front pad towards backward point
fullish outside off stump, Voges comes onto the frontfoot and chips this over point for one out to the sweeper
dropped! Hayden clips a full delivery on the legs out to McMillan on the deep midwicket ropes, but its in and out of his hands...and whats this? Its a no-ball...too much!
back of a length outside off stump, steered down to third man for one
strays down the pads again and Hayden flicks out to deep midwicket for one to keep strike last over
A one-handed six, would you believe it! What a small ground! Hayden gets under a low full toss and sends it over long-off for his tenth sixth, and thats ridiculous!
good length outside off stump, chipped over cover for one
overpitched outside off stump, driven down to long-off
full toss outside off stump, he swings a one-handed shot on that and will only get one to midwicket
fullish delivery outside off stump, Voges slogs that down to long-on to get Hayden back on strike for the final ball

not six, but four! Hayden slams another one-handed shot smack down the ground over Tuffey's head for four, and ends up with the highest individual score for an Australian batsman in an ODI, and he carried his bat to boot!

inn2.comm: bad ball to begin with, well wide down the leg side and its duly called so
another wide as Bracken strives hard for swing and the ball moves away from Vincent's pads
pitches full on about middle and leg and swings too much down leg stump, rapped and they all go up in appeal but ball did too much
good stuff, lands outside off stump and curls into him as he raises the arms
strays down the leg stump and Vincent looks to tickle it fine but ends up with four leg byes
back of a length outside off stump, Vincent walks into the shot but then has to check the shot to mid-off
short of a length outside off stump, Vincent walks into it and pushes it to mid-off for the first run off the bat
good length, swinging delivery outside off stump to which Fleming gets a foot forward and shoulders arms
and he too begins with a wide well down the leg side that Vincent cant get to with the attempted flick, work for Haddin early in the innings
back of a length outside off stump, Vincent gets up and pushes into the cover for the quick single, he's lightfoot but Fleming's slower, in the end he makes it down the other end
good length delivery outside off stump, Fleming drops the hands on the bat and thinks about the quick run but resists as cover swoops in
good length delivery, he brings the back leg across off stump and then plonks the bat down on the ball to smother any late movement
short and wide, and he wristily whips that over midwicket confidently for four, basically dragged that from outside off stump with a lot of bottom hand
super shot! Fleming gets down on bended knee and square-drives the half-volley through point for four more
better ball, on a good length on off stump and Fleming brings the angled bat down in a hurry to defend to the on side
fuller delivery, Vincent comes forward and plays with soft hands, thinking about the scampered single to mid-off
short and wide and he goes after it with a flash of the bat, and the thick edge flies past where second slip could've been and thats four
back of a length and moving into him, he stands and watches it under the eyeline, just dabbing it back past the stumps and calling for the run
good, moving ball lands outside off stump and swings into Fleming, who shoulders arms and lets it pass to Haddin
comes down the track and takes a good length delivery on the rise, square-cutting to backward point on the bounce
again he dances down the track but cant time this at all, hitting with one hand in front of mid-off and sneaking a single
back of a length on off stump, he shuffles across and works that straight to midwicket

what a catch from that man Hodge! Fleming takes a good length delivery from middle and leg and whips it in front of midwicket, but Hodge flings himself acrobatically to his left and pouches the take above his head!
and Tait welcomes him with a nice bouncer down the leg side, but Taylor just ducks under it
shot! Good length delivery on middle and leg, Taylor gets over it and flicks it nicely in the gap at midwicket and gets off the mark with four on this racy outfield
back of a length just outside off stump, he gets over it and taps it into the covers and wants the quick single, well run
back of a length on and around off stump, he gets behind the line and defends back to Tait
back of a length on off stump, he walks into it and defends back to Bracken
back of a length again, this time he waits for it and pushes back to Bracken's left
overpitched outside off stump, he leans forward and drives back down the ground as Bracken collects it
good length on leg stump, he flicks it around the corner past short fine leg for a brace
he chases a swinging half-volley outside off stump, 140ks, and gets beaten
back of a length outside off stump, Bracken knocks the bails off as he bowls, Taylor comes forward and defends
back of a length on the stumps, he shuffles and works that down the ground to mid-on
hoooo! Charges him, and flashes at at a short-pitched delivery and gets enough on it to carry it high over Haddin for four, but gets some words of advice from Tait!

easy catch! Tait strikes with a back of a length, pacy delivery which almost squares up Vincent, who turns the bat in his hands as he looks for runs on the leg side, and the leading egde is easily accepted by Hogg at cover
back of a length on the stumps, he hops up and works that to short midwicket
fires in an attempted yorker at 155ks, its not entirely accurate but Styris somehow manages to get the bat down on it in time, well bowled
quick, back of a length delivery moving in from outside off stump, Styris hops to defend
strays down leg stump, and Taylor whips this backward of square and wants two all the way through, and gets it with ease
reaches forward to a good length delivery outside off stump and drives through the covers, Hussey gives chase and hauls it in
caught and bowled! Taylor is deceived by the slower one, his feet go nowhere and he offers an easy catch back to Bracken, who gleefully laps it up
good length delivery on middle and leg, Fulton stands and works it to square leg
fuller one outside off stump, just, slower too on 120ks, Fulton gets a stride forward and defends
fullish one outside, Fulton gets off the mark with a drive into the covers where Hogg dives, rolls, and stops it in its tracks
full on middle and leg, clipped to Johnson at short midwicket
back of a good length on and around off stump, Fulton stands and drops the hands on it
short of a length outside off stump, he opens the face of the bat and steers that down to third man for a single
good length outside off stump, he walks into a good-looking drive to mid-off
overpitched and he drives back to Tait, who takes it moving to his left
full on middle and leg, flicked to square leg
bad ball, way down the leg side, wide called
good length outside off stump, he leans into it and drives to point
good length on the stumps, he hops and defends back to the bowler
overpitched on and around off stump, he drives to short midwicket
again he reaches for one outside off stump but cant time the drive at all, chopping into the ground in the covers
back of a length on off stump, he stands tall and works the wrists on it to place it to short midwicket
back of a length again, now he drives back down the ground and Bracken gets a hand on it, well bowled all over
edged and gone! Johnson gets rid of Styris first ball with a full, away-swinging delivery that he flashes at loosely, away from the body, and Haddin accepts the regulation nick
lovely ball, sir! This one lands on a sweet spot and goes across him over the top of middle and off and beats him all ends up
full and quite wide, McMillan chases it and is lucky not to get an edge
back of a length down leg stump, he hops and tucks it around the corner to short fine leg to get off the mark
short of a length outside off stump, Fulton gets up on the toes and steers it to backward point
good length on the stumps, gets up and defends to the bowler, ball runs past him for one
good length delivery moving across him and he shoulders arms
good length outside off stump, he eases into the drive to mid-off, Hodge collects the ball and fires in the throw on the nonstriker's stumps, and Fulton is just in....it helps to be a giant of a man
gives him the charge, taking a good length delivery outside off stump and slamming it to mid-on
a yorker on middle and off, and McMillan shuffles to flick it down to fine leg as he knew the man was up, neatly done
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and drives to point with a 'WAIT' back to Fulton
down the wicket he comes, Bracken sees it and tucks him up, McMillan continues down leg and drives into the covers
beaten by one thats slanted past him off a length, Haddin takes it
there's the first six of the New Zealand innings, and 18th of the match! Fulton swivels onto a short of a length delivery on off stump and hammers it over deep backward square leg to bring up the 50
this time he hops up to a short of a length ball on leg stump and tickles it around the gap past backward square for four
good length delivery just outside off stump, Fulton gets forward and defends
fuller one now, and he comes onto it and drives into the covers
short of a length outside off stump, he intentionally runs that down to third man for an easy single
bang, thats four! McMillan swings the bat at a full and wide delivery and creams it over backward point, the man on the ropes moving from third man had no chance to stop it
Watson begins with four wides down leg stump that even Haddin cant get to
back of a length outside off stump, he plays away from his body and drives to point
good length delivery down the leg side, Fulton goes on the backfoot and glances it to backward square leg
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and defends to the off side
good length delivery down leg, McMillan turns it to square leg
fuller and slower, he comes forward and defends to the covers
short of a length outside off stump, Fulton swings in the pull and gets an inside-edge past Haddin and down to fine leg for four
creamed over extra cover! McMillan gives this the kitchen sink and that was almost six, dont give him any room!
better ball, slower and almost in the blockhole, McMillan digs it out
good length and moving across him from off stump, he shoulders arms
strays down leg stump and he works it wide of square leg for a single
slower, back of a length delivery on leg stump, Fulton turns it to short fine leg
short of a length outside off stump, not enough room to cut, he ends up running it to point
fuller ball on off stump, he comes on top of it and turns it to square leg
good length outside off stump, Fulton's feet go nowhere as he drives down the ground, mid-on moves across and fields
back of a length outside off stump, he gets back and drives to mid-off
short one, he gets into position to pull but doesnt time it well, it rolls into midwicket...its a no-ball to boot

comes down the track and swings the bat a shorter one, gets an inside-edge that sneaks past leg stump, Haddin chases it to fine leg where Tait dives, and stops it, only for the 'keeper to kick it over the rope
fuller one on and around off stump, McMillan comes on the frontfoot and defends it
uses the feet again, backing away to leg, and he cant time his slog past point
back of a length outside off stump, Fulton drives to cover
six! Fulton whips a rank half-volley on the legs just over deep backward square leg for half a dozen more..19 sixes and counting!
followed up with a four, as he reaches for a wide delivery and creams and it backward of point for four, well placed
and four more! Fulton's placement is spot-on, as he swivels on the hop to one moving down leg, and works it in the air over square leg
rubbish bowling, top shot! Johnson drops short on leg again and Fulton just swings it down to deep fine leg with a lovely drop-kick shovel shot
now he drives the rank half-volley into the covers, where a good diving stop from White saves four more
overpitched, fractionally, and he chips this powerfully over mid-on for four, Fulton moves to 45!
back of a length delivery outside off stump, he stands rooted and defends in front of point
you can chalk that down as the 20th six of the game, and thats Fulton's 50 in good time! He stands tall and hammers a good length ball smack over long-on for a huge six
swivels on a shorter one and cops one in the stomach area, the ball rolls to the off side
all over! Fulton stands rooted and drives one from just outside off stump to Hussey at short extra cover, and the fun ends for him
short and wide, he cuts aggressively, but cant beat backward point
full down leg side, he looks to flick and its called wide
fraction short, he rocks back and cuts into the covers
dragged one in short, McMillan pulls and the ball lands just in front of square leg
good length delivery on middle and off, he opens the face and defends into the covers
hah! McMillan gets six to his name as he flashes the bat at a 156k lifter and gets a top-edge for four
slower one on a good length, he drops the bat down on it sets off
good length delivery outside the off stump, McMillan opens the face of the bat and plays that to gully
there's McMillan's first, and the 20th of the match! Comes down the track and swings one over wide long-on for maximum
good length outside off stump, he defends into the off side
almost! Faster one moves in off a good length and catches McMillan outside leg stump, on the inner thigh
drifts down leg stump, he shuffles and tickes it fine past short fine leg for four
good length delivery on the stumps, McMillan comes on the frontfoot and plays it back to the bowler
big, bigger, biggest! McMillan uses the feet and slams this, base-ball style, miles over long-on for a huge one
good length outside off stump, driven to mid-off
full and moving well down leg stump, he looks for the flick to fine leg but mistimes it
full toss on middle and off, driven to mid-on
fuller one outside off stump, he plants the leg forward and swings it to mid-on, where Johnson misfields horribly and allows four
banged in short, he swings on one leg and puts the long hop where it should go....all the way to deep fine leg for four
good one! Now he gets some sense and fires in the yorker in the blockhole, which McMillan digs out well
good length, seaming delivery outside off stump, he judges it and shoulders arms
back of a length outside off stump, he gets behind it and defends to cover
well bowled! Pitches and moves off the seam to beat his tame backfoot prod, Haddin collects

good length delivery, he comes forward and checks the shot, sets off for the quick single to mid-off, a throw from Hussey comes into Haddin's end, but where is he? He's gone off on a walk-about, as he expected the throw to go to the other end, and theres an extra run given away...shoddy stuff from Haddin
fuller outside off stump, McCullum reaches for it and slices it down to third man
well done, sir! The yorker in the blockhole, which the batsman digs out
looped up outside off stump, he comes forward and defends
flatter and quicker, he sweeps hard but gets rapped outside the line of off stump
pitches on middle and off and spins into him, he shuffles and picks up one to square leg
tossed up, he comes forward and plays at it outside off stump, misses the line
fizzing up outside off stump, he pokes at it and misses and Haddin cant collect it
smack, and thats his 50! Tossed up, he comes forward and hammers that past mid-off for four, well played!
good length outside off stump, McCullum walks forward and drives
full on the legs, clipped into midwicket for one
overpitched on off stump, he leans into it and drives out to mid-off for one
quick and full on leg stump, he flicks and gets a leading edge over backward point out to third man
too full outside off stump, he latches onto a firm drive but a good diving save by White at cover saves the boundary
back of a length down leg stump, easy pickings for McCullum, who tickles it fine for the single
short and wide, he rocks back and pulls through square leg and the placement is superb, four runs
tossed up outside off stump, he leans forward and defends to cover
tossed up on the stumps, he plans the leg forward and defends
flatter trajectory, he comes half-forward and defends
tossed up, he comes forward and turns it to leg, good bowling this
too full, he gets down and sweeps past square leg for one
overpitched, and he creams it over cover-point for four, and the fun continues
good length delivery outside off stump, he leans into it and drives down towards long-off
beaten by one that angles across him from a good length, he plays at it and gets comprehensively beaten
fuller, he meets it with good footwork and squeezes it to Voges at point, they just manage to pinch the risky single
oh well played! This one was quick and full outside off stump and McMillan jammed the bat down it, deflecting it in the gap behind point and the speedy outfield carries it to the boundary
strays onto middle and leg and McMillan tucks it around the corner for one to end a productive over for New Zealand, who've maintained the run rate at the halfway stage
tossed up outside off stump, swept away out to the deep for one
flatter outside leg stump, McCullum shuffles away and works it around to Johnson at short fine leg
looped up outside off stump, he comes forward and drives wide of point
tossed up outside off stump again, and he sweeps in the air in front of square out to Johnson in the deep
pitches on middle and  leg and he reverse-sweeps down to third man for one
quicker and shorter, comes onto McCullum quicker than anticipated, he shuffles and drives to the on side
tossed up, driven down to long-off for one
fired into middle and leg, comes forward and works it to square leg for the single
tossed up, McMillan dances down the track and flat-bats it down to long-off
fired into middle and leg and McCullum defends back to Voges
tossed up, he uses the feet to drive into the covers
six No. 22! McMillan gives himself room, clearing the front leg, and biffs that with sheer bottom-hand power for another clanger over the sight screen! Top shot!
quicker one, well bowled, McCullum shuffles to off stump and defends to midwicket
slower one on a length, he waits for it and then paddles it into square leg for an easy run
tossed up, comes well forward and defends and sends his partner back as cover swoops in
tossed up, he plants the front leg in line of the ball and sweeps behind square for another single
this one spins in off a good length as the batsman stands erect, and chops it into the ground, some bounce on that ball too
this one spins a mile from outside off stump and McCullum has to withdraw the bat as he thought about chasing it, good bowling from Hogg
good one, full and fast into leg stump and he defends back to Voges
fired in again, he uses the feet and drives out to long-on
tossed up, he gets a stride forward and brings up the 200 with a steered single to point
tossed up again, McMillan gets forward and times the drive in the gap on the off side and picks up a couple
smashed! A full toss outside off stump, he uses the feet well and hits it through the covers for four
looped up down leg stump, he easily works that behind square for one and another good over for the hosts comes to an end
tossed up outside off stump, he uses the feet well to get to the pitch and drive into the covers for one
looped up on off stump, he gets a good stride forward and sweeps through square leg for one
flatter on middle and leg, he shuffles and works it fine for one more
good, looping delivery outside off stump, gets a good step forward and defends into the covers
shorter and he cracks that out to the covers for one
fired in on middle and leg, he drives back to Voges
I'm counting each one for you, and thats 23 sixes today! What a hit on this small ground! McMillian sashays down the track and clubs that over long-on for a big six!

HOLY CRAP, thats out of the stadium! Superb hitting, its like a baseball home run derby! McMillan dances down and lifts Voges miles over the sight screen....24 sixes in the game and McMillan celebrates his 100 with a fiesty pump of the first....immense innings!
tossed up, McMillan comes on the frontfoot and drives it to cover
looped up down the leg side, McCullum goes on the backfoot and glances it to short fine leg
full outside off stump, he leans forward and drives to White at cover
tossed up, he comes forward and drives to cover
looped up down the leg side, McCullum glances it to short fine leg
drifts to leg and he works it to midwicket for one more
flat down the legs, and he just laps it around the corner and the outfield does the rest
tossed up, he comes forward in defence
quicker and flatter, he shuffles and nudges it to square leg
good length ball on off stump, he comes forward with bat and bad married and pushes to mid-off
overpitched outside off stump and he square-drives past point out to the sweeper
fuller one on off stump, he lunges forward and defends and the inside-edge sneaks to square leg
too full down the leg side and he easily clips that past a diving Haddin for four....wides are the call in the end
good response! A rising delivery over the stumps and McCullum arches the back to sway out of the way, good cricket!
good length delivery around off stump, McCullum gets half-forward and drives back to Tait
good ball, pitches full on middle and leg and moves into him, he cant work it fine
tossed up, he comes forward and defends to the on side
spins into him from outside off stump, he rocks back and cuts uppishly to backward point
pitches outside leg stump and he works it around the corner for one

looped up outside off stump, McCullum comes forward and defends to the off side, calls for the run, then sends McMillan back, and he has to turn quickly and dive, and his bat was just inside the line....tense!
wide down the leg stump, spins outside and carries on, Hogg's quicker one goes awry and beats Haddin too
looped up on off stump, he comes forward and defends,pinching a run in front of point
spins away from outside off stump and McMillan stands and chases it, only to get beaten
bounced down the leg side and McCullum ducks under it, 153ks on that delivery, good stuff
short and wide, he cuts hard and the edge goes fine to third man, the 250 comes up
another good lifter outside off stump, McMillan gets out of harm's way, you cannot  play those!
full this time, and he drives past the covers out to the sweeper for one
bounced over leg stump, and thats a crucial dot ball for Australia, intelligent bowling from Tait
full again, McCullum mistimes the ondrive to mid-on
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and defends to point
overpitched and he drives nicely to Bracken at mid-off, good shot for one
bounced on top of middle and off and he sways the back out of the way
now he comes back down the track and collects the good length ball on the full, driving down to long-on
another bouncer over leg stump, McCullum gets down onto his haunches
moves in off a  good length, he takes one hand off the bat and runs it down to third man
good length ball on the stumps, the batsman hops and defends compactly
good length again, he defends off the back foot and picks up one to cover
width offered, but he steers this to point
good length outside off stump, comes forward and defends to the covers
full outside off stump, he drives hard to White at extra cover, who fumbles the collection
overpitched and this time he drives past White and gets one
begins with a short one, angled down leg stump with little bounce, McMillan swivels on one leg and pulls the long hop to fine leg
good length ball moves in from outside off stump, he defends and McCullum sprints down calling the run and they get it
shorter one this time, not enough room to free the arms, he chops it in front of backward point
back of a length on off stump, he gets behind the line and defends with a 'WAIT THERE, MACCA!'
back of a length again, he hops and pushes into the covers off the back foot
good length ball outside off stump, he comes forward and defends into the covers and sends McMillan back
overpitched, McMillan gets to the pitch and drives past the covers
good length again, and he gets to the pitch and drives into the point region
full and wide, he swings at it and misses, Haddin whips off the bails
back of a length on off stump, steered to point and he sends his partner back, very good bowling
bowled! Slower one moves into him, and he has to defend back to Bracken
full toss which he drives down to long-on, just three singles from the over
good length ball on and around off stump, he gets to the pitch and defends to mid-off
banged in short and McMillan pulls in the air over square leg and the ball lands safely in front of the man at deep midwicket, and thats the 150 stand from 135 balls
now he can pull! McCullum gets over another short one and pulls, off one leg, past fine leg and that ball fairly raced away
good length ball outside off stump, he eases into a drive through the off side and gets a couple more to his name
good length ball on the stumps, gets pad and bat together and defends
back of a length, slower one, comes in and he plays it with soft hands to point for one
good length delivery on off stump, he comes forward and defends and sends his partner back
back of a length on leg stump, McCullum works it to square leg to bring up his 50 and Seddon Park erupts
hoooo! Full and wide, McMillan closes his eyes and slashes this over backward point, the ball spirals up and lands just a pace in front of third man
pumped! A fraction full and wide, McCullum clears the front leg and biffs that over mid-off for a one-bounce four
fuller again, angled past him and he has a tickle at it, but the edge falls in front of Haddin, was a slower delivery, so....
overpitched, McCullum leans into a drive past cover-point for one out to the sweeper
fraction wide, and slower, he waits for it and the runs it wide of Haddin down to third man for the single
bowled 'em! Watson strikes! McMillan swings across the line needlessly and misses, and the ball hits middle and off
back of a length on off stump, he stands and defends and escapes with an inside-edge past square leg
good length outside off stump, he plays nice and straight and picks up one into the covers
bounced over the top of middle and leg, he ducks under it
fraction short and he places that with soft hands into the gap in front of point
wide ball, down the leg side
good length ball outside off stump, no room on offer, Franklin comes forward and defends to point
blinder from the debutant! Short and wide, Franklin cuts but cant keep it down, and Voges at backward point dives in the air and snaps it up with two hands moving to his natural left
good length delivery outside off stump, he doesnt get to the pitch but drives to mid-off for a quick single
good length on off stump, he drives back past the stumps to long-off
overpitched outside off stump, Tuffey stands rooted and drives, only to get beaten
edged and it doesnt carry! Tuffey comes forward and drives at a moving delivery outside off stump, and the edge bounces in front of White at slip
beaten by one that moves a shade outside off stump, no footwork, just a tame flirt outside off stump
full again, now he gets over it and opens the face, running it to point for the quick single
back of a length outside off stump, he stands and drives down to mid-off
back of a length outside off stump, stands and glides that wide of point for another quick single
stands and flashes the bat at it, looking to clear the infield, and he does, just, as it lands safely over mid-off's head
crucial runs! Tuffey flashes the bat at a wide one and the thick edge runs down to third man on one bounce
back of a length on off stump, he gets behind the line and presents the full face of the bat back to the bowler
wow! This man is not bothered too much, as he makes room for himself and blasts this back down the ground for six over the sight screen
now here's the cool single, as he comes forward to a good length delivery and pushes in front of point
now he too has a free swing of the arms but his timing isnt as good as McCullum,  and he makes zero contact...reverse swing...?
edged and gone! Tuffey is sucked into driving outside off stump, his bat comes down late and the regulation edge, off the seam movement, is snapped up by Haddin
back of a length delivery, Gillespie looks to run it down but misses
lands on a good length, he comes forward and drives to mid-off
dropped in short on middle and off, he pulls in the gap at midwicket and they scramble two
well bowled! This was slow on a good length just outside off stump, the leg cutter, Gillespie stands and pokes at it and gets an inside-edge past Haddin for two more
the attempted yorker goes awry, ends up a full toss on middle and off, Gillespie stands and pokes at it with an angled bat and the edge races past Haddin for four
runs again! Short of a length delivery on middle and leg, he swings it and gets a french cut off the inner edge of the bat past Haddin again
SHOT! Gillespie! Stand and delivery slog all along the ground past mid-off, just slapped, and McCullum looks at Gillespie with a smile
biffed! Full and straight, McCullum clears the leg and drives straight down the ground, long-off and long-on converge but the batsmen get two anyways, great running
overpitched outside off stump, room on offer, McCullum hits that very hard down to Hogg at long-off, who gets down and fields well
Gillespie you beauty! This one is full and moving into leg stump, Gillespie backs away and squirts the bat at it, and gets another four courtesy the french cut
fast and full, speared into leg stump, he shuffles and nudges it into the gap at midwicket and thats some terrific running
attempted yorker on off stump, he makes room and exposes the stumps, and then jams the bat down to steer it down to third man...Gillespie!
overpitched outside off stump, McCullum leans into it and drives out to cover sweeper for the single...Seddon Park is alive
good ball! Zeroed in on middle and off and McCullum can only dig it out back to Bracken...well bowled
full on middle and leg, he uses the feet to flick to mid-on for one...he sure trusts Gillespie
full on middle and leg, and he plays a very good-looking flick, proper roll of the wrists et al, and gets an easy two out to deep midwicket
slower ball on off stump, now he's just messing with all of us is Gillespie, as he gets over it and flicks over square leg for a couple more
good ball again, well done, great length outside off stump and it beats Gillespie's attempted slash
yorker goes wrong again, ends up full, and Gillespie flicks wide of square leg, wants two, a good throw comes in but Gillespie is home safe
full and wide, he crunches a hard drive to cover
good ball, in the blockhole, McCullum hammers it wide of mid-on for a quick single
short of a length, a bouncer, but Gillespie gets up on the toes and runs that in the gap at gully for one down to third man
full and wide, he makes room and square-drives past backward point, thought about the second but thinks better

run out! Tait bowls a great, low delivery outside off stump, Gillespie squeezes the bat down it to steer it to backward point, crosses for one and then as he turns for the second, has to head back as a very good throw comes in from Voges to get him inches short of his crease
full in the blockhole, McCullum looks to club it, mistimes it to the off side, sets off, Tait and cover swoop in and fire a throw but McCullum is safe
would you believe it? Bracken! He bowls a knee-high full toss on the stumps and McCullum slams that superbly over deep fine leg for half a dozen! What a game this is!
full and he drives that back to the bowler

thats four, and New Zealand have whitewashed, blackwashed, whatever you wanna call it - they've beaten Australia 3-0! McCullum slashes another low full toss, one-handed, smack in the gap behind backward point and since everyone was up, that ball was destined for the ropes!
